        </p>
        <h5>Delivery Performance and Cost Reductions</h5>
        <p>
          <ul class="square">
                <li>OEE has increased from 80.3% in 2008, to 93.3% in 2014.</li>
                <li>Installed capacity has increased from 73.3% in 2008, to 91.5% in 2013. This resulted in additional 575 million cans produced annually.</li>
                <li>Aluminium scrap was reduced from 3.91% in 2008, to 1.48% in 2014.</li>
                <li>Total conversion costs were reduced 24.9% between 2008 and 2014.</li>
                <li>$2.2 million in Lean Enterprise/Six Sigma cost savings from 2012 to 2014.</li>
                <li>Direct Materials usage improved from 2008 to 2014. Ink usage was reduced by 19.8%.</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <h4>People</h4>
        <p>ECA believes that its people are its most important asset. The ECA team started with no can making experience in the country of Guatemala. 97% of the people working at the plant are Guatemalan and developed expertise through a strong commitment to learning and improvement.</p>
        <p>ECA is proud that we have retained and developed 70 team members (122 currently) since the plant startup.</p>
        <p>Our location is used as a training site for methods and processes with our joint venture partners, Rexam plants from the United States, South America and Europe, as well as Envases Universales from Mexico. We enjoy having these people visit our plant because we always learn new things from them.</p>
